    "updated_at": "2019-03-17T22:45:41Z",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "We added https://github.com/grpc/grpc/pull/13561 a while back to provide a utility that automatically adds grpc's dependencies to a project, by that project putting e.g. these lines in their WORKSPACE file:\r\n\r\n```\r\nload(\"@com_github_grpc_grpc//bazel:grpc_deps.bzl\", \"grpc_deps\")\r\ngrpc_deps()\r\n```\r\n\r\nSee [implementation of grpc_deps](https://github.com/grpc/grpc/blob/master/bazel/grpc_deps.bzl#L7) - this adds grpc's c-ares dependency it it doesn't already exist.\r\n\r\nDoes the `grpc_deps()` utility fix the problem for you?\r\n\r\n> Is grpc's ares dependency properly documented for bazel?\r\n\r\nHmm, AFAIK there isn't documentation for grpc's bazel dependencies in any central place. I'm wondering if it would help to add an example for this - consuming grpc from a 3rd party project, via bazel.\r\n"
  },
